frameDefinitions: A generally large group of people, the Combatants, are engaged in a chaotic, violent, and usually protracted Fight amongst themselves.
Some individual or group ceases to be able to sustain an Endeavor (a long-term activity involving economic interaction with the public, often a business venture).
An Astronomical_entity comes into view above the horizon as part of a regular, periodic process of (apparent) motion of the Astronomical_entity across the sky.
An Event continues at a certain Place through Time.
An Entity comes into existence at a particular Place and Time which may take a certain Duration_of_endstate, have a Cause, or be formed from Components.
Partner_1 interacts with Partner_2 (also collectively expressible as Partners) to change their social relationship.
frameExamples: Venus <t>rose</t> at 5:23 AM, twenty minutes before the sun which reached the horizon at 5:43 AM.
Pyongyang agreed to suspend its withdrawal while talks <t>continued</t> with Washington.
Problems may <t>arise</t> whenever an S1 sophont enters the game.
I <t>befriended</t> the little pony by giving him a piece of apple.
